extends includes/layout

append head
  title Installation - jQuery Rondell

append content
  include includes/submenu
  mixin submenu('Installation')

  br
  .center
    h2 Installation
  hr
  br

  div
    h6 Prequisites

    ul
      li
        b
          a(href="http://www.jquery.com", target="_blank", title="jQuery library") jQuery
        | &nbsp;
        span.label.important Important
        br
        | 1.5.2 or better
        br
        | Provided with the download.

      li
        b
          a(href="http://www.modernizr.com", target="_blank", title="Modernizr library") Modernizr
        | &nbsp;
        span.label.warning Optional but recommended
        br
        | This library tests the browser for feature support and provides this information to the plugin and stylesheets.
        br
        | We use this for css fallbacks in our themes and touch detection.
        br
        | Provided with the download.

      li
        The 
        b jQuery mousewheel plugin
        | &nbsp;
        span.label.notice Optional
        br
        | If you want to use the mouse horizontal scroll events to control the rondell.
        br
        | Provided with the download.
      
      li
        b
          a(href="http://fancybox.net/", target="_blank", title="jQuery library") jQuery fancybox 1.3.4
        | &nbsp;
        span.label.notice Optional
        br
        | If you want to have a lightbox like in some of my examples. You can use a different one too, but this on has been tested.
        br
        | Provided with the download.

    :markdown
      The plugins are provided in the *lib* folder. 
      
      If you don't want to use the *Modernizr* library you should remove the
      *.cssgradients*, *.borderradius*, *.rgba* and *.boxshadow* classes 
      in *css/jquery.smallipop.css* to have css3 effects.
    
    br
    
    h6 Required files

    :markdown
      * Copy *js/jquery.rondell.js* to your javascript folder.
      * Copy *js/jquery-x.x.x.min.js* to your javascript folder if you don't use jQuery already.
      * Copy *js/modernizr-x.x.x.js* to your javascript folder if you don't use modernizr already.
      * Copy *css/jquery.rondell.css* to your css folder.
    
      There are minified versions of the rondell files for production in the *lib* and *css* folders too.
    
    br
    
    h6 Modify your html header
    
    p.
      Add these lines to the header (or footer in case of the javascripts) 
      of your html file and replace x.x.x with the correct versions.

    pre
      &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/jquery.rondell.css" type="text/css" media="all" title="Screen"/&gt;
      &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery-x.x.x.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;   
      &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="js/modernizr-x.x.x.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;   
      &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery.rondell.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</pre>

    br
    
    :markdown
      #### Get started!

      Setup your images html and use the code of one of my examples to 
      create your own rondell.

      Experiment with the various options and send me a message if you want 
      to share your great work.
            
  br.clear


